commit message: Remove svn:executable that all files had by accident.
updated project files to newer SDK conventions so that it imports into Eclipse cleanly now
Fix a crash when there's a paired device that returns a null Bluetooth class.
A workaround for some older devices where using the standard createRfcommSocketToServiceRecord() method always causes connect() to fail. If it fails we try createRfcommSocket via reflection.
Manifest version bump for Play Store release. Also set targetSdkVersion=16 so that we look nice on modern devices and use the action bar for menu.
